16
00:01:34,991 --> 00:01:37,161
All alone with nowhere to go in my life

17
00:01:37,161 --> 00:01:39,931
I need your love

18
00:01:39,931 --> 00:01:43,231
I'm a broken rose

19
00:01:43,231 --> 00:01:46,171
Oh baby, help me from frozen pain

20
00:01:46,171 --> 00:01:50,121
With your smile, your eyes,
and sing me, just for me

21
00:01:50,871 --> 00:01:53,101
I wanna need your love

22
00:01:53,711 --> 00:01:56,331
I'm a broken rose

23
00:01:56,511 --> 00:01:58,671
I wanna need your love

24
00:02:10,221 --> 00:02:11,151
I'm broke!

25
00:02:11,661 --> 00:02:12,781
Naturally.

26
00:02:16,501 --> 00:02:19,771
But why? I worked so hard
and saved up before coming here,

27
00:02:19,771 --> 00:02:22,001
yet I only have 2,228 yen left.

28
00:02:22,131 --> 00:02:24,471
If you spend your money,
it runs out.

29
00:02:25,771 --> 00:02:30,571
You went on this crazy spending splurge
of clothes and furniture.

30
00:02:30,641 --> 00:02:33,411
But Mr. Mizukoshi gave me a good deal
on everything I got from there.

31
00:02:33,651 --> 00:02:35,211
On top of that, rather than cash,

32
00:02:35,211 --> 00:02:37,381
he offered to deduct the amount for
the clothes I got from my salary.

33
00:02:37,521 --> 00:02:40,751
That's why you didn't have much of
a salary to bring home last month.

34
00:02:40,851 --> 00:02:42,321
That's right! Isn't it horrible?!

35
00:02:42,451 --> 00:02:44,791
- Was I tricked, you think?!
- You did it to yourself!

36
00:02:45,021 --> 00:02:47,261
What about you? Do you have
enough money to get by, Nana?

37
00:02:47,261 --> 00:02:50,351
You don't have a full-time job,
just temporary stuff from time to time.

38
00:02:50,701 --> 00:02:53,791
Unlike you,
I don't waste my money.

39
00:02:53,901 --> 00:02:56,131
- Thank goodness.
- Don't rely on someone else's money!

40
00:02:56,201 --> 00:02:57,691
I have no intention of doing so.

41
00:02:57,801 --> 00:02:59,291
Then what did you mean?

42
00:02:59,541 --> 00:03:01,871
You see, if we both didn't have money,
that leads to anxiety, don't you think?

43
00:03:01,941 --> 00:03:04,201
You are relying on my money!
Don't count on it!

44
00:03:04,881 --> 00:03:08,211
We agreed to split the rent
for this place, exactly half-half.

45
00:03:08,611 --> 00:03:10,621
If you can't make arrangements
for funds by the end of the month,

46
00:03:10,621 --> 00:03:12,021
I'm kicking you out.

47
00:03:13,851 --> 00:03:14,781
- You devil!
- Huh?!

48
00:03:15,221 --> 00:03:17,451
It wouldn't bother you if I lay
in the streets dying, would it, Nana?!

49
00:03:17,661 --> 00:03:18,881
Dying once may do you good!

50
00:03:19,791 --> 00:03:21,051
Please, don't abandon me!

51
00:03:21,131 --> 00:03:22,861
Let go of me!
I'll be late for work.

52
00:03:23,061 --> 00:03:23,691
Work?

53
00:03:24,131 --> 00:03:25,701
What kinda work are you doing
at this hour of the night?

54
00:03:25,701 --> 00:03:26,961
Is it an S&M club?

55
00:03:27,201 --> 00:03:28,561
What do you care?

56
00:03:28,771 --> 00:03:31,031
Have a good night with
the ghosts.

57
00:03:33,341 --> 00:03:34,531
No way...

58
00:03:37,811 --> 00:03:40,401
No. This is no time to be
afraid of ghosts.

59
00:03:40,711 --> 00:03:42,041
My problem is money.

60
00:03:42,721 --> 00:03:45,811
There's over half a month
until my next payday.

61
00:03:45,981 --> 00:03:47,781
Will I survive on 2,000 yen?

62
00:03:48,251 --> 00:03:50,191
What am I to do?
This is getting scary.

63
00:03:51,121 --> 00:03:52,591
Having no money is scary!

64
00:03:54,691 --> 00:03:58,091
I didn't come to Tokyo
to experience this!

65
00:03:58,301 --> 00:04:00,791
Then why did you come?

66
00:04:05,771 --> 00:04:06,901
To make it on my own?

67
00:04:07,041 --> 00:04:08,801
Then solve this on your own.

68
00:04:09,111 --> 00:04:10,101
But how?

69
00:04:10,211 --> 00:04:11,571
That's for you to figure out!

70
00:04:11,641 --> 00:04:13,801
But I don't know how
to be a dominatrix!

71
00:04:13,881 --> 00:04:14,811
A dominatrix?

72
00:04:15,051 --> 00:04:18,211
Talk to Shoji and have him feed you
until the end of the month.

73
00:04:18,421 --> 00:04:19,351
I can't do that.

74
00:04:19,451 --> 00:04:22,021
If I talk to Shoji about this
he'll hate me,

75
00:04:22,021 --> 00:04:23,651
and no longer wanna be
with me, for sure.

76
00:04:24,161 --> 00:04:27,331
Also he's very busy with work
and his studies at university,

77
00:04:27,331 --> 00:04:29,761
so I'd only be a nuisance
bothering him at this late hour.

78
00:04:29,831 --> 00:04:31,231
You got that right!

79
00:04:31,831 --> 00:04:34,421
I get it, Nana. So don't cry.

80
00:04:34,571 --> 00:04:36,691
Use this to hold you over
until the end of the month.

81
00:04:40,511 --> 00:04:41,371
Kyosuke!

82
00:04:41,511 --> 00:04:43,301
We cannot afford that!

83
00:04:43,411 --> 00:04:45,881
I'm not giving it to her.
It's just a loan.

84
00:04:46,011 --> 00:04:46,751
No way.

85
00:04:46,751 --> 00:04:50,511
Give Nana cash, and you're certain
it'll be all gone in a day.

86
00:04:50,681 --> 00:04:52,451
That's a cruel thing to say,
Jun-chan.

87
00:04:53,851 --> 00:04:55,051
- What?
- Rice.

88
00:04:55,821 --> 00:04:57,881
My parents sent me some.
I'll share it with you.

89
00:04:58,361 --> 00:05:00,421
You can feast on this
until the end of the month.

90
00:05:03,001 --> 00:05:07,301
No way! No way! No way!

91
00:05:08,031 --> 00:05:09,431
Hey, what about meat and
vegetable dishes?

92
00:05:12,371 --> 00:05:15,031
It's all right.
Calm down and think.

93
00:05:16,711 --> 00:05:18,771
My next payday is on the 26th.

94
00:05:20,411 --> 00:05:24,281
If I don't buy anything from the store,
I'll receive at least 70,000 yen.

95
00:05:25,151 --> 00:05:27,051
But I'll be debited for my cell phone,

96
00:05:27,051 --> 00:05:29,021
so I should deposit 10,000
in my bank account.

97
00:05:29,721 --> 00:05:31,021
That leaves me with 60,000.

98
00:05:32,391 --> 00:05:34,431
I only need to pay half the rent
and utility bills,

99
00:05:34,431 --> 00:05:35,981
so 60,000 should be
more than enough.

100
00:05:36,861 --> 00:05:38,261
Hey, not a problem.

101
00:05:39,201 --> 00:05:40,961
But I'll only have a little left over.

102
00:05:41,431 --> 00:05:43,561
And I'll hafta survive another
full month with that little amount.

103
