131
00:07:03,521 --> 00:07:05,921
I really think you should pick
your friends more carefully.

132
00:07:06,021 --> 00:07:08,321
But like I said,
she's usually a really good girl.

133
00:07:08,421 --> 00:07:09,651
I don't believe that.

134
00:07:12,061 --> 00:07:12,681
Ow!

135
00:07:14,291 --> 00:07:14,821
Yo!

136
00:07:20,301 --> 00:07:21,631
I get it.

137
00:07:21,931 --> 00:07:24,431
Well, I was just as surprised.

138
00:07:24,901 --> 00:07:27,671
You have the same employer,
go to the same university,

139
00:07:27,671 --> 00:07:29,161
and enroll at the same faculty.

140
00:07:29,241 --> 00:07:31,611
Guess you pretty well
hafta get along.

141
00:07:31,741 --> 00:07:34,081
Yes, but Sachiko was accepted
on her first try,

142
00:07:34,081 --> 00:07:35,271
so she's two years younger.

143
00:07:35,381 --> 00:07:36,071
Sachiko?

144
00:07:37,221 --> 00:07:39,681
I can't help it. She asked me
to call her that.

145
00:07:39,951 --> 00:07:41,081
There was no reason to refuse.

146
00:07:41,191 --> 00:07:45,421
She's clearly your type.
Petite and fair-skinned.

147
00:07:45,721 --> 00:07:46,711
