Hey!

256
00:14:37,641 --> 00:14:40,041
You knew you would hafta run
for the last train.

257
00:14:40,571 --> 00:14:42,271
So why did you hafta wear
those shoes?

258
00:14:56,861 --> 00:14:57,821
I did it on purpose.

259
00:15:08,571 --> 00:15:10,631
Nana

260
00:15:16,841 --> 00:15:17,401
Hello?

261
00:15:18,111 --> 00:15:19,971
Shoji!

262
00:15:20,651 --> 00:15:22,741
Help me!

263
00:15:34,591 --> 00:15:36,291
This is for the taxi.

264
00:15:37,101 --> 00:15:39,531
Never mind.
It's on my way home, anyway.

265
00:15:39,901 --> 00:15:42,771
But It was my fault
we missed the last train.

266
00:15:42,931 --> 00:15:44,201
It really is okay.

267
00:15:51,281 --> 00:15:53,451
Shoji, that call earlier.

268
00:15:53,451 --> 00:15:54,741
It was from your girlfriend, right?

269
00:16:01,451 --> 00:16:04,751
It's my policy not to accept such money
from a guy who has a girlfriend.

270
00:16:14,171 --> 00:16:15,191
Good night.

271
00:16:35,221 --> 00:16:38,311
It appears that this is
all the money I have right now.

272
00:16:39,891 --> 00:16:42,991
Why? You're always working
so hard.

273
00:16:43,191 --> 00:16:45,061
You really are spending it all
on Sachiko!

274
00:16:45,501 --> 00:16:47,801
You're wrong!
In fact, I bought that!

275
00:16:51,641 --> 00:16:53,571
A computer. And it's a Mac.

276
00:16:53,641 --> 00:16:57,571
Nice, isn't it? I'm studying
computer graphic design, after all.

277
00:16:58,111 --> 00:16:59,131
I wonder if we can get
a good price for it.

278
00:16:59,241 --> 00:17:00,141
Cut it out!

279
00:17:00,411 --> 00:17:03,071
But how else am I gonna get
proper food from tomorrow!

280
00:17:03,381 --> 00:17:04,111
All right!

281
00:17:04,421 --> 00:17:05,401
I'll share this with you.

282
00:17:05,681 --> 00:17:07,341
Pickled plums my grandma
made herself.

283
00:17:08,421 --> 00:17:10,181
Shoji, you idiot!

284
00:17:10,591 --> 00:17:12,351
You're of no use!

285
00:17:16,191 --> 00:17:19,031
So, now that I was unemployed,
I was lost,

286
00:17:19,031 --> 00:17:23,561
seriously contemplating the possibility
of starving to death in the streets.

287
00:17:26,201 --> 00:17:27,831
300,000 yen?!

288
00:17:28,441 --> 00:17:29,441
That's right!

289
00:17:29,441 --> 00:17:32,771
Mr. Mizukoshi deposited
300,000 yen for severance pay!

290
00:17:33,081 --> 00:17:34,841
Are you sure you that's not 30,000?

291
00:17:35,111 --> 00:17:37,741
Your remaining salary would've
amounted to around that much.

292
00:17:37,921 --> 00:17:40,011
Then do you think this 300,000 yen
is to sever his relationship with me?

293
00:17:40,491 --> 00:17:42,041
Did you sleep with Mizukoshi?

294
00:17:42,121 --> 00:17:43,951
- No way!
- You're lying!

295
00:17:44,161 --> 00:17:46,121
Why would he give you
that much if you didn't?!

296
00:17:46,221 --> 00:17:47,491
It's not a lie!

297
00:17:47,631 --> 00:17:49,591
Mr. Mizukoshi is returning
to his hometown

298
00:17:49,591 --> 00:17:50,691
and will be getting married.

299
00:17:50,861 --> 00:17:53,061
I feel that I've been deceived.

300
00:17:53,331 --> 00:17:54,491
- You idiot.
- Huh?

301
00:17:55,371 --> 00:17:57,931
The one who deposited
the 300,000 yen wasn't Mizukoshi.

302
00:17:58,441 --> 00:17:59,771
Take a closer look.

303
00:18:01,071 --> 00:18:03,471
Natsuko Komatsu.
That's my mom!

304
00:18:03,681 --> 00:18:05,481
You're a long way from independence

305
00:18:05,481 --> 00:18:07,241
if you're crying to your parents
for money.

306
00:18:07,351 --> 00:18:11,011
Huh? But I didn't tell
I was having money problems!

307
00:18:11,281 --> 00:18:14,011
I thought, if I told them
they would make me go back home.

308
00:18:16,821 --> 00:18:18,151
How did she know?

309
00:18:19,391 --> 00:18:20,861
Could it be maternal instinct?

310
00:18:28,631 --> 00:18:29,461
Oh, right.

311
00:18:29,971 --> 00:18:33,431
Hey, Nana. Now I've got all this money,
let's celebrate with sukiyaki tonight.

312
00:18:33,571 --> 00:18:34,001
Huh?

313
00:18:34,441 --> 00:18:36,271
Back home, my mom would
make sukiyaki

314
00:18:36,271 --> 00:18:37,711
when we had something
to celebrate.

315
00:18:37,981 --> 00:18:39,711
Let's go back to the supermarket
to buy what we need.

316
00:18:39,811 --> 00:18:40,711
You...

317
00:18:40,951 --> 00:18:43,001
You're unemployed!
What is there to celebrate about?!

318
00:18:43,151 --> 00:18:44,671
The fact that I got money...

319
00:18:44,781 --> 00:18:45,481
Don't celebrate!

320
00:18:45,481 --> 00:18:47,041
Be remorseful for the money
you've wasted!

321
00:18:47,391 --> 00:18:50,121
We're having natto soybeans
tonight as planned.

322
00:18:50,721 --> 00:18:53,211
You're not eating any meat
until you find a job.

323
00:18:54,031 --> 00:18:54,991
No way!

324
00:19:01,001 --> 00:19:04,701
Say, shouldn't you call Natsuko
and thank her?

325
00:19:05,771 --> 00:19:07,261
I'll do it later.

326
00:19:08,041 --> 00:19:10,741
Oh, I see. If you call now,
you'd be embarrassed

327
00:19:10,741 --> 00:19:12,511
because you'll cry the moment
you hear mommy's voice.

328
00:19:12,781 --> 00:19:14,281
Well, sure.

329
00:19:14,281 --> 00:19:17,341
You get homesick too, sometimes,
don't you Nana?

330
00:19:17,421 --> 00:19:20,411
No. Since I don't have a home.

331
00:19:21,991 --> 00:19:25,391
There you go, trying to be cool again.

332
00:19:52,821 --> 00:19:55,681
Tonight calls for sukiyaki, after all!

333
00:20:07,801 --> 00:20:12,791
Yasu, Blast is the band you started.

334
00:20:14,871 --> 00:20:17,901
Yeah. I was so worried
I couldn't sleep at night.

335
00:20:19,711 --> 00:20:22,741
Besides, there are law firms
in Tokyo too.

336
00:20:46,071 --> 00:20:47,201
Hey, Nana...

337
00:20:48,511 --> 00:20:53,211
Do you still think that
you don't have a home anywhere?

338
00:20:56,851 --> 00:21:00,151
This dinner table by the window,
and the chairs.

339
00:21:00,791 --> 00:21:04,351
They're still there,
just as they were back then.

340
00:21:07,861 --> 00:21:12,851
I reached into the sky

341
00:21:12,961 --> 00:21:19,371
But I couldn't reach what I wanted

342
00:21:19,571 --> 00:21:24,741
They grew smaller
and disappeared into the sky

343
00:21:24,741 --> 00:21:30,741
Like colorful balloons

344
00:21:30,921 --> 00:21:32,851
I'm alone

345
00:21:32,851 --> 00:21:36,581
My hand had no place to go

346
00:21:36,751 --> 00:21:43,221
And gently you took it

347
00:21:43,331 --> 00:21:44,401
Starless night

348
00:21:44,401 --> 00:21:48,591
I won't look back
at the shadow of my past

349
00:21:48,831 --> 00:21:54,401
I want to feel your warmth

350
00:21:55,011 --> 00:21:56,271
Tears are falling down

351
00:21:56,271 --> 00:22:00,411
Even if I'm unsure I won't let go

352
00:22:00,411 --> 00:22:06,871
Of your hand holding mine

